---
description: Pull request title and body format
alwaysApply: false
---

# Title

- PR titles must match: `^(feat|fix|bug|chore|refactor|docs|test|hotfix)(\([a-z0-9_-]+\))?: .+$`
- The first character must be the commit type; do not prefix titles with gitmojis or other characters.
- A gitmoji MUST appear inside the subject immediately after the colon (e.g., `feat(ui): ✨ add new dashboard component`).

# Body

- PR bodies must include: **Summary**, **Changes**, **Validation**, **Deployment impact**, and **Notes**.
- Fill `.github/pull_request_template.md` with concrete content; do not submit the raw template text.

# Submission

- Use `gh pr create --base develop --assignee @me --title "<type(scope): <gitmoji> subject>"`.
- Keep each PR strictly focused on one specific logical task or coherent change set.
- STRICTLY avoid mixing behavior changes with large formatting-only diffs or unrelated features.
